Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] In preparing for brisk North-South trade, the 
government has decided to exchange North Korea's currency that 
may be obtained in travel to North Korea through a third country 
and in trade with North Korea, at the Export-Import Bank. It 
was learned that on 24 February, the government has deposited 
300 million won as North-South cooperation funds at the 
Export-Import Bank. An official of the Export-Import Bank 
revealed: The funds were deposited for exchange with North 
Korean currency in preparation for brisk North-South trade. 

